    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once starting to soften, increase the heat to high, then add your <strong>pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and cook for a further 5-6 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
