      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>smoked paprika  </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, then cook for a further 2 min or until fragrant and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>While the pork is cooking, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and finely shred</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
